---
import ProseLayout from '../layouts/ProseLayout.astro';
---

<ProseLayout
  title="Terms of service — Casebound"
  description="Casebound terms of service. The agreement covering your use of the Casebound app and casebound.co."
  canonicalUrl="https://casebound.co/terms"
>
  <h1 class="font-serif font-medium text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-2">Terms of service</h1>
  <p class="text-casebound-muted text-sm mb-8"><em>Last updated: May 28, 2026.</em></p>

  <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-casebound-gold pl-4 text-casebound-muted text-[15px] mb-8 italic">
    This document is in interim form pending review by counsel and will be updated before public launch.
  </blockquote>

  <p class="mb-6">
    These terms are an agreement between you and Pixel Master Technologies LLC ("we," "us," "our") covering your use of the Casebound app and casebound.co. By creating an account or using Casebound, you agree to these terms.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Eligibility</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    You must be at least 13 years old to use Casebound. If you're under 18, you confirm that a parent or guardian has agreed to these terms on your behalf where required by local law.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Your account</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Provide accurate information when you create an account. Keep your password secure. You're responsible for activity under your account. We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Your content</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Your library, lists, reading sessions, notes, and other content remain yours. You grant us a limited license to store, process, and display your content as required to operate the service.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Anonymized metadata corrections you submit (e.g., a corrected page count) may improve the shared book metadata cache for all users. This is a deliberate design decision.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Acceptable use</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Don't:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
    <li>Use Casebound to infringe anyone's copyright or other rights.</li>
    <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the service.</li>
    <li>Send malicious or excessive traffic.</li>
    <li>Harass other users (when light social features arrive in a later version).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Subscriptions and billing</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Casebound has a free tier and a paid tier ("Pro"). Pro is billed monthly ($4.99) or annually ($29.99) via Apple, Google, or RevenueCat. Subscriptions auto-renew at the end of each period unless canceled before then.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Cancel any time via your Apple, Google, or RevenueCat account settings. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period. Refunds are handled by the payment platform according to its policies.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Service "as is"</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Casebound is provided as is. We work hard to keep it reliable, but we can't guarantee it'll be uninterrupted or error-free. We don't warrant that book metadata is accurate &mdash; we cache from public sources and rely on user corrections.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Limitation of liability</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    To the extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages, or for lost data, lost profits, or lost goodwill. Our total liability to you for any claim related to the service will not exceed the amount you've paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim, or $50, whichever is greater.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Termination</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    You can stop using Casebound and delete your account at any time. We may suspend or terminate accounts for violations of these terms or for prolonged inactivity (we'll notify you first when feasible). On account deletion, your personal data is removed per the Privacy Policy.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Governing law</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    These terms are governed by the laws of the State of [Jurisdiction &mdash; confirm with attorney, placeholder Delaware], USA, without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Disputes will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in that jurisdiction.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Changes</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    We'll update these terms as the service evolves. Material changes will be announced in-app and via email if you have notifications enabled. Continued use after a change constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Contact</h2>

  <p class="mb-2">
    <a href="mailto:support@pixel-master.com" class="text-casebound-green underline underline-offset-4">support@pixel-master.com</a>
  </p>

  <p class="text-casebound-muted text-sm">
    Pixel Master Technologies LLC
  </p>
</ProseLayout>
